{
  "answer": "The matla (opening couplet) of Ghalib's ghazal is:\n\n> کب وہ سنتا ہے کہانی میری  \n> اور پھر وہ بھی زبانی میری[^1]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nKab woh sunta hai kahani meri  \nAur phir woh bhi zabani meri[^2]\n\n**Translation:**  \nHe never hears the story I maintain is mine;  \nAnd even spoken, the attempt in vain is mine.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 102 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/original/#p-f1ea96).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 102 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/transliteration/#p-10bd3c). *(Note: Verse follows frontmatter; first poetic line aligns here.)*\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 102 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/translation/#p-a9dedb).",
